column1: #Text=According to medical workers and witnesses , at least 20 people , including many civilians , have been killed in Somalia 's capital of Mogadishu after one of the heaviest battles between Islamist militants and government forces in weeks .
#Text=Ali Muse , the head of Mogadishu 's ambulance services , said at least 58 other people were wounded .
#Text=Other reports put the number of injured as high as 70 .

#Text=Witnesses say the shelling began on Thursday at the city 's international airport , as President Sharif Shekh Ahmed was heading to Uganda for an African Union meeting on refugees and internally displaced people .
#Text=The witnesses said that insurgents shot mortars at the airport and airplane and African Union peacekeepers returned fire .
#Text=They say the busy Bakara market was also struck hard by mortar shells .
#Text=Witnesses saw the dead bodies of at least six civilians there .
#Text=The president was not hurt in the attack .

#Text=“ As the Somali president flew out to Kampala for a meeting of African presidents , Islamist insurgents began shelling the airport , ” said a spokesman for the presidency in an interview , Abdulkadir Mohamed Osman .

#Text=Vice chairman of the Elman Peace and Human Rights Organization in Mogadishu Ali Yasin Gedi said that " insurgents fired mortar bombs at the plane carrying President Ahmed , and then AMISOM [ the African Union Mission to Somalia ] responded with shells .
